            <pb n="1"/> 
            
            <p>Montreal 2d January 5621.<lb/>
                My dear Sir&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>It has been from no<lb/> want of appreciation of your<lb/> kindness in writing me the<lb/> acceptable words of condolence<lb/> you did&#44; that I have not<lb/> sooner thanked you for them.<lb/>  My loss has been no ordinary<lb/> loss.  In very truth he was<lb/> the best of parents&#8212;and a man of<lb/> such thorough and varied<lb/> learning that were I not his<lb/> son I must have revered him<lb/> knowing him as well as I did.<lb/>  His meekness and retiringness<lb/> caused the world to know not<lb/> a tithe of his excellence&#59; but<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>the extraordinary respect and<lb/> grief manifested by the London<lb/> Jewish community sephardim<lb/> ashkenazim and Reformers<lb/> showed &#38; this is my consolation&#8212;all loved<lb/> him all respected him&#8212;and<lb/> in my most intense grief as<lb/> in my calmer hours I had<lb/> the fullest assurance&#8212;an<lb/> assurance and confidence so<lb/> complete that I bless God for<lb/> it and receive it as his merciful<lb/> utterings&#44; and that is my<lb/> revered beloved father is enjoying<lb/> that state which he entreated<lb/> from on high so often for others<lb/> and that he is now resting<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Thank God&#44; his widow and<lb/> family have found warm sympathising<sic></sic><lb/> friends&#44; and I believe it is contemplated<lb/> to place my brother Saml in<lb/> the office of assistant Hazan.<lb/>  He has been in training for the<lb/> Ministry for some years&#44; and<lb/> obtained highest honors at the<lb/> &#34;Jews College.<lb/></p>
            <p>Pray express Mrs De Sola&#39;s<lb/> and my kindest greetings to<lb/> Mrs Morais and believe me<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear sir<lb/>
                Your&#39;s very truly<lb/>
                Abraham de Sola<lb/>
                The Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                &#38;c &#38;c &#38;c<lb/>
            </p>
            
        </body>
